    dcterms:description """
  An arcsecond, also called a $\\textit{second of arc}$, is a unit of angle equal to $1/60$ arcminutes, or 1/1296000 of a turn.
  The recommended symbol for the arcsecond in the is the $\\textit{double prime}$ ($''$).
